	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Apr 8th 7:41 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.25]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I only realized you were on FV after i told ya to save up for a Wurmmy. However I have no idea how the economics work on FV. I have a level 5 bard on that server I never went back to only for the reason that I didn't want to leave my freinds on Tunare. Aside from that I love the whole concept.<br><br>So the question is, since there isn't much coin in FV how much would a Wurmslayer go for if you ever did find someone selling it? As for fighting in Paw you'd be amazed at how much coin you can make there. When you hit 30 or so you can start to solo the gnolls yourself and with them dropping 1-4pp plus a FS weapon every now and then your coin can build up pretty quickly.<br><br>What weapons are you using? With a full group you could start trying Goblins on the third floor in Runnyeye. They can drop a Black alloy Longsword which is 10/29 +3 svp. Great stats, especially since it's attainable at around your level. I also remember a good sword dropping in befallen that was no drop which you could get at around the same level. I can't remember the name of it though, sorry.<br><br>As for strategy on how to play a warrior. I think the longer you play a warrior the more you'll come to learn your own strategies. I really can't tell you where to start. Timing your taunts and slams is definately one thing as you mentioned and can save your party if you do it right. Last night I was helping my friend finish off the last part to the Cloak of Truth quest and out of the last 4 spells the cleric casted I interuppted 3 of them. Fortunately the one I didn't interupt was a smite and not a CH. (Not sure if he does CH but I didn't want to find out!)<br><br>Other strategies include carrying around different equipment for different scenarios. Using clickable items, questing for ones that could come in useful etc and knowing when to use them. When fighting a caster, switch to resist gear if you have some. <br><br>Always hit from the back when you are not main assist! Mobs (as are you) are more vulnerable from behind. You hit for ore and miss less. whe there's a rogue with you stand off to the side still aiming for the back. Just make sure you're not in the rogues way though.<br><br>Non-large races should carry a shield around for when fighting casters. And try and keep bash up as much as possible. As I stated before slam might have saved my friends and I last night and since those smaller guys don't get that incredible ability they should at least be able to bash the casters.<br><br>Create hotkeys for your weapons and armour. This is for quick changing. I used to do this a lot with switching weapons back and forth. (I'd equip the Scimitar of Ethereal Energy and the Longsword of ethereal energy for high MR when fighting casters). This is usually a necessity for bards but there's no reason why we can't do it and benefit from it.<br><br>That's all I can think of for now.<br><br><br><br><br>&nbsp;<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=234170" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=234170</a><br><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=235432" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=235432</a><br><br>Shadow of the Dragon<br>Tunare<br>(www.eqsod.com)</td></tr>
